 Book Management System (Java)
 Project Overview

The Book Management System is a Java-based application developed using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts and Custom Exception Handling.

The system manages book records, validates book details such as price and genre, groups books according to genre, and calculates the average price of books.

This project demonstrates clean class structure, constructor overloading, exception handling, and collection usage in Java.

Features

Default constructor

Parameterized constructors

Constructor overloading

Custom checked exceptions

Separate exception handling for invalid genre and invalid price

ArrayList to store multiple Book objects

Display complete book details

Group books according to genre

Calculate average price of books

No user input required

 Project Structure

The project consists of the following Java files:

Book.java

InvalidPriceException.java

InvalidGenreException.java

ArrayListOfBooks.java

 Book Class Description

The Book class represents a book entity with the following attributes:

Name

Author Name

Price

Publisher Name

Genre

ISBN

Date of Publishing

The class includes:

A default constructor that initializes book details with default values.

A parameterized constructor that validates price and throws an exception if the price is negative.

A parameterized constructor that validates both genre and price.

Proper data validation using custom exceptions.

 Custom Exceptions

Two custom checked exceptions are implemented:

InvalidPriceException
This exception is thrown when the price of a book is negative.

InvalidGenreException
This exception is thrown when the genre entered is not among the allowed categories such as fiction or autobiography.

 Program Functionality

The main class performs the following tasks:

Creates Book objects

Handles invalid genre and invalid price separately using try-catch blocks

Stores valid books in an ArrayList

Displays all book details

Groups books according to their genre

Calculates and displays the average price of all stored books

🎯 Learning Outcomes

This project helps in understanding:

Object-Oriented Programming concepts

Constructor overloading

Custom exception creation

Checked exception handling

ArrayList usage

Nested looping for grouping data

Basic aggregation logic (average calculation)

Exception propagation

🛠 Technologies Used

Java (JDK 8 or above)

Java Collections Framework

OOP Concepts

Command-line execution

 How to Run

Compile all Java files in the project.

Run the main class file.

The program will execute and display book details, grouped genres, and the average price.

